stylometry: Our group project we wanted to determine if we would bring in enough revenue on a regular basis in order to pay our 5 employees $15 an hour.  By doing some research we determined the cost of each item in our bakery and took the highest price and lowest price of each category (i.e. types of cakes) to determine the average price and then multiplied the price by the amount that we knew we would sell each week. We determined our fixed costs such as rent, utilities, and employee wages, and our variable costs such as supplies, ingredients, etc. Between our costs, revenue, and demand we determined our profit and ran goal seek to determine the minimum and maximum we could pay our employees each hour and we found that our profit was high enough that we could pay them $15 an hour.  From our project I learn how many different things need to be considered when running a business, especially how many costs there are. We tried to keep our problem as simple as possible and we still ran into frequent problems. However, since owning a bakery is a realistic goal of mine, I learned the basics of excel and can use it to determine future scenarios if I decide to go through with owning my own business.
